<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="32" type="multiple">
<paragraph blockId="11.[332,1263,392,1737]" pageId="11" pageNumber="32">
This neotropical species, very close to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fabricius, 1775)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1775" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Dichelops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="furcatus" subGenus="Diceraeus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="32">D. (D.) furcatus</emphasis>
(Fabricius, 1775)
</taxonomicName>
was captured on very few occasions, and no nymphs or eggs were found on privet. Like other species, it is probably an occasional visitor of this tree. Adults brownish-green dorsally and green ventrally. Females 12.5 mm (n = 10) long, and males 11.0 mm (n = 10). Early instars brown and later instars brownish-green.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[332,1263,392,1737]" box="[396,648,540,564]" pageId="11" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1837" baseAuthorityName="Dallas" baseAuthorityYear="1851" box="[396,648,540,564]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Dichelops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melacanthus">
<emphasis box="[396,648,540,564]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="32">Dichelops melacanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[332,1263,392,1737]" pageId="11" pageNumber="32">
is reported to occur on soybean in Brazil (
<bibRefCitation author="CORSO, I. C." box="[1111,1250,540,564]" journalOrPublisher="EMBRAPA" pageId="11" pageNumber="32" pagination="152 - 157" refId="ref5952" refString="CORSO, I. C. 1984. Constatacao do agente causal da mancha-de-levedura em percevejos que atacam a soja no Parana. In: SEMINARIO NACIONAL DE PESQUISA DE SOJA, 3, Anais ... Campinas, EMBRAPA. p. 152 - 157." title="Constatacao do agente causal da mancha-de-levedura em percevejos que atacam a soja no Parana" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="SEMINARIO NACIONAL DE PESQUISA DE SOJA, 3, Anais ..." year="1984">CORSO, 1984</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="AVILA, C. J. &amp; PANIZZI, A. R." box="[332,574,569,593]" journalOrPublisher="Anais Soc. ent. Brasil, Londrina" pageId="11" pageNumber="32" pagination="193 - 194" part="24" refId="ref5746" refString="AVILA, C. J. &amp; PANIZZI, A. R. 1995. Occurrence and damage by Dichelops (Neodichelops) melacanthus (Dallas) (Heteroptera: Pentatomidae) in corn. Anais Soc. ent. Brasil, Londrina, 24 (1): 193 - 194." title="Occurrence and damage by Dichelops (Neodichelops) melacanthus (Dallas) (Heteroptera: Pentatomidae) in corn" type="journal article" year="1995">ÁVILA &amp; PANIZZI (1995)</bibRefCitation>
reported an unusual massive attack of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dallas" baseAuthorityYear="1851" box="[974,1138,568,593]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Dichelops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melacanthus">
<emphasis box="[974,1138,568,593]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="32">D. melacanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on seedling corn in the western State of Mato Grosso do Sul and in Paraná. The bugs feed on stems, causing yellowing of leaves and seedling death. It may also attack wheat plants. These attacks on corn and wheat occur in areas under no-tillage because adults, which feed on soybean, stay on the ground beneath crop residues after harvest and will feed on the following crop.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
